IDENTIFICATION ERROR: No matching hull signature.

Primary registry [CORRUPTED]. Drive signature predates scan by 0.1 seconds. Classification assessment pending - 98% match, Brillant-class.

Attempting heuristic classification... Result: "Impossible."

// CAUSAL VIOLATION DETECTED // AUTO-SCRUB INITIATED

REMAIN CALM. DO NOT observe the vessel directly. DO NOT engage under any circumstance.

[AIO INTERNAL - ABOVE STRATOSPHERIC]

Limited temporal displacement falls far from the Sunsetter's; however, the Asuia shows promise for mass production, 'logistically feasible' even. Standard FCS and targeting requires adjustment; time dilation proves difficult to overcome without direct integration with [OCTANTIS]. Send the reports through, I'm sure it has a solution prepared already.

Integration trials with [OCTANTIS] have yielded anomalous efficiencies - flux vents cycling 15% ahead of projected timelines, as if the ship anticipates overload before it manifests. We've noted crew disorientation in sim-runs: echoes of commands issued seconds before they're spoken, shadows of maneuvers that resolve into reality. Recommend psychological conditioning protocols for deployment batches. If [OCTANTIS] can stabilize the dilation bubble without fracturing causality, the Asuia could redefine ambush doctrine. The Office has authorized Phase II prototyping; Tri-Tachyon liaisons are pressing for data shares, but the Office will redact temporal metrics.

// Addendum, deleted from record:
// "The latest sim-feed from [OCTANTIS]... It's not just predicting. The Asuia prototype engaged [REDACTED] in trial, but the logs show damage patterns from weapons that weren't fired until after the kill."
// "Causality bleed. We've seen it in the deep-core interfaces before - [OCTANTIS] pulling threads from some unknown subroutines. If we push this, we're not building ships; we're unraveling the present."
// "August knows, doesn't he, surely?"
// "He suspects. But survival demands it. The Rift won't shield us forever."

IDENTIFICATION ERROR: No matching hull signature.

Primary registry [CORRUPTED]. Drive signature predates scan by 0.3 seconds. Damage assessment returns paradoxical values - structural integrity reads 47% and 98% simultaneously.

Attempting heuristic classification... Result: "Impossible."

// CAUSAL VIOLATION DETECTED // AUTO-SCRUB INITIATED

REMAIN CALM. DO NOT observe the vessel directly. DO NOT engage under any circumstance.

[AIO INTERNAL - ABOVE STRATOSPHERIC]

Sunsetter-class trials continue to exceed parameters. Temporal displacement allows the vessel to occupy probability states 0.2 to 0.7 seconds removed from baseline causality. Targeting solutions become obsolete before ordnance arrives. The hull integrates replacement components from its own prior states - regenerating from damage that "hasn't happened yet."

Integration with [OCTANTIS] proceeds on schedule. Crew report that operating the Sunsetter is "intuitive" in ways difficult to articulate to supervisors.

We believe this is a feature.

// Addendum, deleted from record:
// "I watched Meridian-7. The Sunsetter took devastating fire. Then it didn't."
// "Something is choosing which version of events gets to be real."
// "But, why does it keep choosing us?"
